1
00:00:34,617 --> 00:00:37,954
UNDERCOVER MISS HONG

2
00:00:53,011 --> 00:00:54,220
Stay still.

3
00:00:54,304 --> 00:00:56,639
-Hurry up and hand these out too.
-Yes, sir.

4
00:00:56,723 --> 00:00:58,892
-Is it centered?
-It's perfect right now.

5
00:00:58,975 --> 00:01:00,477
Hey, this is backwards.

6
00:01:00,560 --> 00:01:01,561
You're looking into a mirror.

7
00:01:01,644 --> 00:01:04,397
Oh, you're right. "Over my dead body."

8
00:01:04,481 --> 00:01:07,358
But if I'm being honest,
I support financial reforms.

9
00:01:07,942 --> 00:01:10,070
All of it needs to be upended.

10
00:01:14,949 --> 00:01:15,784
What is it?

11
00:01:17,077 --> 00:01:18,703
What's that around your head?

12
00:01:18,787 --> 00:01:19,954
Does it make me look old?

13
00:01:20,038 --> 00:01:21,289
Man, you're something else.

14
00:01:21,372 --> 00:01:24,584
Look at you, clawing your way back
to the head office to save your ass.

15
00:01:25,376 --> 00:01:27,712
How dare you suck on a candy
in front of the director?

16
00:01:28,713 --> 00:01:30,507
My roommate told me
to eat one at a time like this.

17
00:01:30,590 --> 00:01:31,424
You got a problem?

18
00:01:31,508 --> 00:01:33,092
Share if you have extra.

19
00:01:41,017 --> 00:01:41,851
What's this?

20
00:01:42,894 --> 00:01:43,728
Resignation…

21
00:01:47,941 --> 00:01:48,900
Hey, kid.

22
00:01:49,484 --> 00:01:51,486
That's just how things are
in the real world.

23
00:01:51,569 --> 00:01:53,655
You need to know
how to own your failures--

24
00:01:53,738 --> 00:01:54,989
Who said I failed?

25
00:01:56,950 --> 00:01:58,535
I'm not done yet.

26
00:02:03,540 --> 00:02:04,749
Why you…

27
00:02:05,416 --> 00:02:07,418
Please process my resignation quickly.
I'll be off.

28
00:02:08,002 --> 00:02:08,837
What?

29
00:02:09,420 --> 00:02:10,713
Hey, take this back…

30
00:02:10,797 --> 00:02:13,091
Stop! Hong Keum-bo!

31
00:02:13,174 --> 00:02:14,300
Hold on!

32
00:02:20,348 --> 00:02:21,558
Stop her! Hong Keum-bo!

33
00:02:21,641 --> 00:02:24,144
Hong Keum-bo! You can't resign!

34
00:02:24,227 --> 00:02:26,980
Not over my dead body!

35
00:02:27,063 --> 00:02:28,565
Did Ms. Hong just resign?

36
00:02:28,648 --> 00:02:29,482
Yeah.

37
00:02:30,525 --> 00:02:31,359
She quit.

38
00:02:32,277 --> 00:02:33,403
Why is she quitting?

39
00:02:35,530 --> 00:02:37,574
She must be getting married.
That has to be it.

40
00:02:38,449 --> 00:02:40,660
An older single woman
would only quit like that

41
00:02:40,743 --> 00:02:42,495
when she's getting married.

42
00:02:46,583 --> 00:02:47,417
Taxi!

43
00:02:53,423 --> 00:02:55,800
-Damn it.
-Hong!

44
00:02:55,884 --> 00:02:58,261
Sir, take me to Hanmin's head office.
I'll pay you double.

45
00:02:58,344 --> 00:03:00,013
Hong, wait! Stop!

46
00:03:02,682 --> 00:03:04,559
-Oh no.
-Why you…

47
00:03:11,232 --> 00:03:12,442
I'm coming with you.

48
00:03:12,942 --> 00:03:15,862
Damn it! Who said you could quit?

49
00:03:15,945 --> 00:03:18,072
-Put your seatbelt on.
-What? Seatbelt?

50
00:03:18,156 --> 00:03:20,825
Who cares about seatbelts right now?

51
00:03:20,909 --> 00:03:21,993
Why won't this pull out?

52
00:03:22,660 --> 00:03:25,872
Hey, are you protesting
because things didn't go your way?

53
00:03:26,706 --> 00:03:28,625
This country's economy is in peril.

54
00:03:28,708 --> 00:03:30,627
Nobody cares about
a chairman embezzling money.

55
00:03:31,210 --> 00:03:32,795
They're not going to pursue it!

56
00:03:33,463 --> 00:03:34,797
How can you not understand that?

57
00:03:34,881 --> 00:03:36,049
Given the economic crisis,

58
00:03:36,132 --> 00:03:40,011
they're willing to let charges like
illegal slush funds and tax evasion slide.

59
00:03:40,845 --> 00:03:44,098
Turning a blind eye like this
only lets the big crooks run wild.

60
00:03:44,766 --> 00:03:47,393
The higher-ups letting them slide
are basically accomplices.

61
00:03:47,936 --> 00:03:48,770
Accomplices?

62
00:03:48,853 --> 00:03:50,897
You must be joking. Watch it!

63
00:03:51,856 --> 00:03:54,817
INVESTMENT AGREEMENT
INVESTMENT AMOUNT: 300 BILLION WON

64
00:03:58,154 --> 00:03:59,948
KANG PIL-BEOM

65
00:04:06,329 --> 00:04:07,163
All right.

66
00:04:13,544 --> 00:04:14,504
KANG PIL-BEOM

67
00:04:18,299 --> 00:04:19,300
Here.

68
00:04:22,845 --> 00:04:24,138
My goodness.

69
00:04:25,181 --> 00:04:27,058
Thank you.

70
00:04:28,059 --> 00:04:29,310
-Great.
-Thank you, sir.

71
00:04:31,104 --> 00:04:32,730
It was a pleasure.

72
00:04:34,440 --> 00:04:35,441
Thanks.

73
00:04:50,999 --> 00:04:54,085
Chairman Kang won't change his mind
now that the smoke's cleared, right?

74
00:04:54,669 --> 00:04:57,547
Hanmin can't even cover
the promissory notes due in two weeks.

75
00:04:57,630 --> 00:04:58,798
They keep up appearances,

76
00:04:58,881 --> 00:05:00,717
but they're a house of cards
at this point.

77
00:05:02,093 --> 00:05:03,511
Even now,

78
00:05:03,594 --> 00:05:06,931
I think your decision
to target Korea next was spot-on.

79
00:05:08,516 --> 00:05:11,227
I guess you enjoyed the report
from the "advance scout."

80
00:05:11,811 --> 00:05:13,021
Most definitely.

81
00:05:14,105 --> 00:05:16,441
Chairman Kang may try to rein us in later,

82
00:05:16,524 --> 00:05:18,192
given that he's naturally distrustful.

83
00:05:18,276 --> 00:05:21,863
I'll have the shell company we set up
start buying up bonds as well.

84
00:05:22,989 --> 00:05:24,073
Okay.

85
00:05:24,657 --> 00:05:27,368
Are there any issues
like someone you're wary of?

86
00:05:29,203 --> 00:05:30,204
There was someone,

87
00:05:31,372 --> 00:05:32,206
but I took care of it.

88
00:05:36,294 --> 00:05:37,295
The IMF crisis has emerged

89
00:05:37,378 --> 00:05:40,965
as a major variable,
shaking up the 15th presidential election.

90
00:05:41,466 --> 00:05:44,677
The candidates continue to fiercely debate
over who bears responsibility,

91
00:05:44,761 --> 00:05:48,556
calling for a reckoning
within both parties and pressing voters

92
00:05:48,639 --> 00:05:50,475
to demand accountability
at the ballot box.

93
00:05:51,059 --> 00:05:52,101
Experts say major variables

94
00:05:52,185 --> 00:05:55,146
will remain in flux
until the election's final days.

95
00:05:55,229 --> 00:05:57,190
As we reach the final stretch…

96
00:05:57,273 --> 00:05:58,816
I'm going to become a major variable.

97
00:05:58,900 --> 00:06:00,318
Sir, you can drop me off up ahead,

98
00:06:00,401 --> 00:06:02,862
and please drive him back to the FSS.

99
00:06:02,945 --> 00:06:04,614
Where are we?

100
00:06:04,697 --> 00:06:05,531
Hey, where are we?

101
00:06:06,365 --> 00:06:08,284
What about the fare?
I didn't bring my wallet.

102
00:06:08,868 --> 00:06:11,537
Just call Nam Dong-gi down
once you've arrived at the office.

103
00:06:12,288 --> 00:06:13,331
Hey! Hold on a second.

104
00:06:13,414 --> 00:06:15,541
-Sir, can't you roll the window down?
-Bye.

105
00:06:15,625 --> 00:06:17,460
Hey, wait! Hong!

106
00:06:17,543 --> 00:06:19,587
I hope you trip and fall!

107
00:06:20,505 --> 00:06:21,881
Hong Keum-bo!

108
00:06:29,514 --> 00:06:31,349
EPISODE 10: CLASH OF THE TITANS

109
00:06:32,433 --> 00:06:35,144
I went into the FSS today

110
00:06:35,770 --> 00:06:37,146
and saw Hong Keum-bo.

111
00:06:37,647 --> 00:06:38,481
It's her.

112
00:06:38,564 --> 00:06:42,527
She's the one that came to the auto shop
with Chairman Kang's grandson.

113
00:06:43,444 --> 00:06:44,320
Really?

114
00:06:44,987 --> 00:06:46,906
She came in today
and handed in her resignation.

115
00:06:48,157 --> 00:06:51,369
People were talking about
her getting married or something.

116
00:06:52,745 --> 00:06:55,623
Her boss followed her out
and begged her to stay,

117
00:06:55,706 --> 00:06:57,333
but she never looked back once.

118
00:06:58,042 --> 00:06:59,919
She must've known it was a lost cause.

119
00:07:00,670 --> 00:07:02,380
It seems she's not a complete idiot.

120
00:07:03,381 --> 00:07:06,050
But how does Hong Keum-bo and Albert Oh

121
00:07:06,884 --> 00:07:08,302
know each other?

122
00:07:09,011 --> 00:07:10,179
Well?

123
00:07:10,263 --> 00:07:12,765
Should I dig deeper into Hong Keum-bo?

124
00:07:14,934 --> 00:07:16,853
What could she possibly do
without her title?

125
00:07:25,945 --> 00:07:26,946
No.

126
00:07:29,824 --> 00:07:32,285
Her car must have been there for a reason.

127
00:07:33,911 --> 00:07:35,788
Try tailing Albert.

128
00:07:37,039 --> 00:07:39,083
We need concrete evidence
to get rid of Albert

129
00:07:39,667 --> 00:07:42,170
and ensure a sure push for Nora
as the next president.

130
00:08:27,507 --> 00:08:28,549
EMPLOYMENT AGREEMENT

131
00:08:28,633 --> 00:08:30,259
This is your new employment contract.

132
00:08:31,928 --> 00:08:33,679
Even amid difficult economic conditions,

133
00:08:33,763 --> 00:08:36,349
we fought to preserve jobs
for our female staff,

134
00:08:37,225 --> 00:08:40,186
but the recent round of restructuring
was an inevitable decision.

135
00:08:40,853 --> 00:08:43,606
We hope you understand
that these new measures are designed

136
00:08:43,689 --> 00:08:47,777
to strengthen internal cohesion
and help prevent future layoffs.

137
00:08:48,569 --> 00:08:51,113
"Contract employment.
Terminable at any time."

138
00:08:51,197 --> 00:08:53,199
"One female employee for three divisions."

139
00:08:54,784 --> 00:08:56,619
So they'll work us to the bone, huh?

140
00:08:56,702 --> 00:08:59,413
After stamping your seal or thumbprint,
leave the contracts here

141
00:09:00,414 --> 00:09:01,874
and return to your divisions.

142
00:09:03,417 --> 00:09:04,961
Collect them and bring them to me.

143
00:09:05,044 --> 00:09:06,504
Yes, ma'am.

144
00:09:21,477 --> 00:09:24,313
Being away from your post too long
will reflect poorly on all of us.

145
00:09:24,397 --> 00:09:26,524
Stamp your seals and return at once.

146
00:09:37,743 --> 00:09:39,120
What if it didn't burn?

147
00:09:41,330 --> 00:09:44,083
By the will of the heavens,
it ended up in my hands.

148
00:09:47,003 --> 00:09:48,337
Not a chance, Queen Bee.

149
00:09:50,256 --> 00:09:52,425
You'll be laden with honors
if you return with that.

150
00:09:52,925 --> 00:09:53,759
No.

151
00:09:54,343 --> 00:09:55,469
I'm going to steal it all.

152
00:09:56,721 --> 00:09:57,722
Are you in?

153
00:10:00,725 --> 00:10:02,059
You're not reporting it to the FSS?

154
00:10:02,727 --> 00:10:05,688
I already did, but the higher-ups
have no intention to pursue it.

155
00:10:06,606 --> 00:10:08,441
Given that we're in an economic crisis,

156
00:10:08,524 --> 00:10:10,484
corporate corruption
is apparently off the table.

157
00:10:11,611 --> 00:10:13,529
The higher-ups are always the issue.

158
00:10:14,113 --> 00:10:15,948
I want to steal all of this money

159
00:10:16,032 --> 00:10:18,951
to oust the corrupt controlling
shareholder and complicit executives,

160
00:10:19,035 --> 00:10:20,828
and save Hanmin's employees.

161
00:10:22,747 --> 00:10:24,749
You saw the ledger,
so you know I can't do it alone.

162
00:10:25,374 --> 00:10:28,336
You said you only went after dirty money.

163
00:10:30,880 --> 00:10:32,506
Then again, Hanmin's slush fund

164
00:10:33,299 --> 00:10:35,217
is the dirtiest money I've ever seen.

165
00:10:37,386 --> 00:10:40,097
You have three days to decide.
I hope you're in.

166
00:10:40,848 --> 00:10:41,682
Also,

167
00:10:41,766 --> 00:10:43,517
I can stay with Mi-sook tonight.

168
00:10:44,060 --> 00:10:45,102
I'm off to work now.

169
00:11:01,369 --> 00:11:02,787
EMPLOYEE NAME: HONG…

170
00:11:43,494 --> 00:11:46,497
Didn't you say Hong Keum-bo would return
to the FSS on December 8th?

171
00:11:46,580 --> 00:11:47,706
LETTER OF RESIGNATION

172
00:11:48,457 --> 00:11:51,794
I have that kid to blame
for my migraine right now.

173
00:11:52,378 --> 00:11:54,213
She showed up at the office today

174
00:11:54,755 --> 00:11:56,757
and threw a resignation letter in my face.

175
00:11:56,841 --> 00:11:58,050
A resignation letter?

176
00:12:00,177 --> 00:12:01,262
Director Yun.

177
00:12:01,846 --> 00:12:03,472
Are you sure
you're not hatching another plan?

178
00:12:03,556 --> 00:12:05,975
You put her to work again, didn't you?

179
00:12:07,393 --> 00:12:08,727
Why you little…

180
00:12:09,228 --> 00:12:10,563
You think she'd listen to me?

181
00:12:10,646 --> 00:12:11,730
Don't you know her?

182
00:12:12,231 --> 00:12:15,651
I wouldn't even be talking
if I had some sort of decent plan.

183
00:12:15,734 --> 00:12:17,611
What could she even do there by herself?

184
00:12:17,695 --> 00:12:19,947
She's just being stubborn right now!

185
00:12:20,614 --> 00:12:23,075
Don't get me riled up.
It's making my headache worse.

186
00:12:25,369 --> 00:12:27,997
She won't even answer my calls right now.

187
00:12:28,080 --> 00:12:31,834
Can you just sweet-talk her
into coming back here?

188
00:12:31,917 --> 00:12:34,420
-Director Yun!
-Just utilize your charm.

189
00:12:34,503 --> 00:12:35,671
I'm sure you can do it.

190
00:12:35,754 --> 00:12:38,007
Jeez, could you be any more frustrating?

191
00:12:43,971 --> 00:12:44,847
Damn it.

192
00:12:48,767 --> 00:12:52,313
SUCCESS WILL NOT WAIT FOR YOU

193
00:13:07,995 --> 00:13:11,040
Why are you cracking a book here
when you've never been much of a reader?

194
00:13:12,333 --> 00:13:15,669
You're surprisingly relentless
with maintaining your public image.

195
00:13:15,753 --> 00:13:17,171
You're 17 minutes late.

196
00:13:17,254 --> 00:13:18,214
I don't have much time.

197
00:13:18,297 --> 00:13:19,298
I'll give you ten minutes.

198
00:13:19,882 --> 00:13:21,342
I must say I'm curious.

199
00:13:21,425 --> 00:13:23,928
Why did you ask to see me out here?

200
00:13:24,011 --> 00:13:27,139
We're under constant surveillance
at the office and at the house.

201
00:13:28,349 --> 00:13:29,225
I'm talking about Oh Deok-gyu.

202
00:13:30,434 --> 00:13:31,268
Oh Deok-gyu?

203
00:13:32,895 --> 00:13:35,773
He's been flipping out
ever since my daughter and I moved in.

204
00:13:35,856 --> 00:13:38,484
He might have a hulking body
and giant bug eyes,

205
00:13:38,567 --> 00:13:40,152
but he's the pettiest man alive.

206
00:13:40,736 --> 00:13:43,614
I'm thinking about securing a position
for Ms. Kang at the company.

207
00:13:44,490 --> 00:13:46,325
Why? Did the chairman tell you to?

208
00:13:47,493 --> 00:13:50,829
You're scared you'll be kicked out
if Oh Deok-gyu becomes president,

209
00:13:51,830 --> 00:13:53,916
so you'll use Nora and me
to shield yourself?

210
00:13:54,542 --> 00:13:56,043
We're in the same boat.

211
00:13:56,919 --> 00:13:59,713
After all, Mr. Oh's nemesis is you.

212
00:14:01,048 --> 00:14:03,092
I can persuade the chairman.

213
00:14:04,510 --> 00:14:07,805
How about officially introducing
Ms. Kang to the company

214
00:14:08,430 --> 00:14:12,017
with a carefully crafted résumé
that's impressive enough to position her

215
00:14:12,601 --> 00:14:13,894
as a successor?

216
00:14:15,980 --> 00:14:17,356
Hold on a second.

217
00:14:17,439 --> 00:14:19,441
Since Albert is a division manager,

218
00:14:19,525 --> 00:14:21,235
my Nora should be ranked higher.

219
00:14:21,318 --> 00:14:22,570
Give her something higher.

220
00:14:22,653 --> 00:14:24,280
And she should have her own big office.

221
00:14:25,948 --> 00:14:28,075
Let's discuss the details over a meal.

222
00:14:28,659 --> 00:14:29,702
Shall we?

223
00:14:29,785 --> 00:14:31,161
Then I'll have the full-course meal.

224
00:14:33,247 --> 00:14:34,081
Okay.

225
00:14:34,164 --> 00:14:34,999
Excuse me.

226
00:14:41,171 --> 00:14:43,048
RISK MANAGEMENT, RESEARCH,
CONFERENCE ROOM

227
00:14:48,804 --> 00:14:50,097
FEMALE STAFF DUTY ASSIGNMENT

228
00:14:50,180 --> 00:14:51,473
HONG JANG-MI: RESEARCH, TRADING, IT

229
00:14:58,772 --> 00:15:00,524
RECEIPTS FOR EXPENSE REPORTS

230
00:15:04,403 --> 00:15:07,197
Hong Jang-mi, you dared to humiliate me?

231
00:15:08,616 --> 00:15:11,660
An amateur would've wiped you out
with the rest of the layoffs.

232
00:15:11,744 --> 00:15:14,663
However, I'm more than that.

233
00:15:14,747 --> 00:15:18,459
I'll pay back that day's humiliation
with double the interest.

234
00:15:25,424 --> 00:15:27,551
Have this translated
by 8:30 a.m. tomorrow.

235
00:15:28,135 --> 00:15:29,094
Hey!

236
00:15:29,178 --> 00:15:31,430
The company is struggling,
yet you're wasting paper.

237
00:15:31,513 --> 00:15:33,140
Use scrap paper for that.

238
00:15:33,223 --> 00:15:34,767
I am using scrap paper.

239
00:15:34,850 --> 00:15:35,684
Hey!

240
00:15:36,226 --> 00:15:38,145
Look at all those numbers.

241
00:15:38,228 --> 00:15:41,023
Security is essential.
You can't just use any old document.

242
00:15:42,441 --> 00:15:43,359
Seriously?

243
00:15:43,442 --> 00:15:45,194
Does he expect me to harvest papyrus then?

244
00:15:47,613 --> 00:15:48,781
Stop glaring.

245
00:15:49,365 --> 00:15:50,908
Ms. Hong, you're always…

246
00:15:50,991 --> 00:15:52,159
Just look at all this.

247
00:15:52,242 --> 00:15:54,662
You're always unprepared
for even your basic duties.

248
00:16:02,711 --> 00:16:05,631
From nine to noon, the Research Division.

249
00:16:05,714 --> 00:16:08,217
From noon to three, the Trading Division.

250
00:16:08,300 --> 00:16:09,593
And from three to six, the IT Division.

251
00:16:09,677 --> 00:16:11,679
Those are my assigned duty hours.

252
00:16:12,262 --> 00:16:14,848
If you'll excuse me,
I'll head to the Trading Division now.

253
00:16:17,810 --> 00:16:18,852
Hey!

254
00:16:18,936 --> 00:16:21,313
You don't get to tell me when you work!

255
00:16:21,397 --> 00:16:22,940
You'll work after hours if you have to.

256
00:16:23,774 --> 00:16:27,695
Why should I devote my time to a company
that could drop me at a moment's notice?

257
00:16:29,530 --> 00:16:30,823
What the…

258
00:16:34,201 --> 00:16:35,661
Get back to work.

259
00:16:38,664 --> 00:16:43,460
I swear, one day,
I'll wipe that smugness off your face,

260
00:16:43,544 --> 00:16:45,462
even if it's the last thing I do here.

261
00:16:45,546 --> 00:16:46,672
Damn it.

262
00:16:54,221 --> 00:16:57,891
Shouldn't we check with the boss
whether to scale back trading on this?

263
00:16:58,851 --> 00:17:00,561
Come on, what would Stoobert know?

264
00:17:01,353 --> 00:17:02,354
Who's "Stoobert"?

265
00:17:03,731 --> 00:17:05,315
Albert the "Stooge" Division Manager.

266
00:17:05,899 --> 00:17:07,609
"Stoobert" for short.

267
00:17:23,208 --> 00:17:24,168
Hello?

268
00:17:32,509 --> 00:17:34,303
Why make me come all the way here?

269
00:17:35,429 --> 00:17:37,681
Director Yun told you to return
on December 8th.

270
00:17:37,765 --> 00:17:39,391
Why are you still here?

271
00:17:40,392 --> 00:17:42,352
You care way too much
about other people's jobs.

272
00:17:42,936 --> 00:17:46,190
Ms. Song has hired someone
to go after Hong Keum-bo,

273
00:17:46,273 --> 00:17:48,567
so get out of here
before you land yourself in trouble.

274
00:17:50,652 --> 00:17:53,781
I should've insisted on firing you
during the restructuring.

275
00:17:55,032 --> 00:17:56,325
You really are the worst.

276
00:17:56,867 --> 00:17:58,827
You'd fire me over a personal vendetta?

277
00:17:58,911 --> 00:18:00,370
Personal?

278
00:18:00,454 --> 00:18:03,332
I'm only trying to eliminate
a risk factor as management.

279
00:18:04,708 --> 00:18:08,253
Did it ever occur to you that I could
easily expose you for identity theft?

280
00:18:09,630 --> 00:18:11,173
No, never.

281
00:18:12,758 --> 00:18:15,928
You'll also be in trouble
if people learn about our past together.

282
00:18:16,011 --> 00:18:17,930
Maybe you've been abroad for too long,

283
00:18:18,013 --> 00:18:20,599
but Koreans eat up romantic entanglement.

284
00:18:20,682 --> 00:18:21,767
Romantic entanglement?

285
00:18:21,850 --> 00:18:25,437
The moment you expose my identity,
you'd be blowing yourself up too.

286
00:18:27,231 --> 00:18:28,857
Unless you want messy gossip around you

287
00:18:28,941 --> 00:18:31,902
and end up on Chairman Kang's bad side,
keep your mouth shut.

288
00:18:32,528 --> 00:18:34,655
This is a threat, just so you know.

289
00:18:42,412 --> 00:18:44,248
What is she thinking?

290
00:18:48,794 --> 00:18:49,753
Chairman.

291
00:18:50,254 --> 00:18:52,673
They say vitamins
help you feel energized in the morning.

292
00:18:52,756 --> 00:18:54,216
-Enjoy.
-Jeez.

293
00:18:54,925 --> 00:18:55,926
Let's see.

294
00:19:02,349 --> 00:19:03,559
It's not bad.

295
00:19:03,642 --> 00:19:04,476
Right?

296
00:19:06,311 --> 00:19:07,604
Right.

297
00:19:07,688 --> 00:19:10,899
It looks like
Nora's still off in dreamland.

298
00:19:12,109 --> 00:19:13,735
Did she forget she now lives with elders?

299
00:19:13,819 --> 00:19:16,196
She still has a lot of growing up to do.

300
00:19:16,697 --> 00:19:18,699
Beauties run on extra sleep,
didn't you know?

301
00:19:20,701 --> 00:19:23,787
Albert must get his looks from his mother.

302
00:19:23,871 --> 00:19:25,914
He wouldn't be falling asleep
if he took after his dad.

303
00:19:28,292 --> 00:19:30,169
I wasn't sleeping!

304
00:19:32,004 --> 00:19:33,839
Oh, right.

305
00:19:33,922 --> 00:19:36,383
Have you set a date
for Nora's first day of work?

306
00:19:37,801 --> 00:19:41,180
She'll be starting next Monday,
and we're preparing a press release.

307
00:19:41,263 --> 00:19:42,472
Good.

308
00:19:42,556 --> 00:19:44,266
What? Nora's first day?

309
00:19:45,058 --> 00:19:46,018
At our company?

310
00:19:46,101 --> 00:19:46,977
No.

311
00:19:47,728 --> 00:19:49,980
Not at your company, but at our company.

312
00:19:52,065 --> 00:19:53,609
We live in a competitive society.

313
00:19:54,776 --> 00:19:58,655
The sharpest one with the most potential

314
00:19:58,739 --> 00:20:00,490
will become my successor.

315
00:20:01,074 --> 00:20:02,242
Of course.

316
00:20:09,041 --> 00:20:09,875
Oh gosh.

317
00:20:28,227 --> 00:20:30,646
Ms. Kang will be
starting work here next week.

318
00:20:32,189 --> 00:20:34,107
She'll be a director, not a staff member,

319
00:20:34,191 --> 00:20:35,192
so she'll need her own office.

320
00:20:36,860 --> 00:20:39,446
Madam Choi will inspect it closely
and be ready to nitpick,

321
00:20:39,529 --> 00:20:41,406
so make sure it's properly set up.

322
00:20:42,491 --> 00:20:43,951
Yes, ma'am.

323
00:20:46,620 --> 00:20:50,624
She'll be frequenting the 12th floor
to prepare for Ms. Kang's engagement.

324
00:20:51,416 --> 00:20:55,170
Just let Admin and the front desk know
about Madam Choi's visits.

325
00:20:55,254 --> 00:20:56,380
An engagement?

326
00:20:57,047 --> 00:20:58,131
With President Shin?

327
00:21:08,350 --> 00:21:09,851
You saw her this morning.

328
00:21:09,935 --> 00:21:13,730
As if that ditzy, naive girl
could ever become a successor.

329
00:21:13,814 --> 00:21:17,776
Kang Nora's mere existence is
nowhere near meeting the qualifications.

330
00:21:17,859 --> 00:21:19,403
I'm not exactly qualified either.

331
00:21:20,153 --> 00:21:22,281
Son, have some confidence.

332
00:21:22,364 --> 00:21:23,615
Be a man.

333
00:21:23,699 --> 00:21:24,574
Dad.

334
00:21:24,658 --> 00:21:26,618
I just know myself and my place well.

335
00:21:26,702 --> 00:21:27,577
Why you…

336
00:21:30,539 --> 00:21:33,542
We need to deal with Kang Nora
pushing her way in.

337
00:21:34,251 --> 00:21:35,711
I mean, she's about to be engaged,

338
00:21:35,794 --> 00:21:37,921
so why does she suddenly need a new title?

339
00:21:38,005 --> 00:21:38,922
Oh, boy.

340
00:21:39,006 --> 00:21:41,925
If President Shin joins her side,
things will get messy.

341
00:21:45,804 --> 00:21:47,889
The patient's name is Kim Mi-sook, right?

342
00:21:48,515 --> 00:21:51,310
-Yes.
-Here's the total amount due.

343
00:21:51,393 --> 00:21:52,477
MEDICAL EXPENSE STATEMENT
TO BE PAID: 674,500 WON

344
00:22:02,612 --> 00:22:03,697
I'll pay the full amount.

345
00:22:04,406 --> 00:22:05,240
Sure.

346
00:22:19,254 --> 00:22:20,380
She paid the hospital bill.

347
00:22:22,007 --> 00:22:25,010
As if it's not infuriating enough
that his daughter was right under my nose.

348
00:22:25,927 --> 00:22:28,805
Hospital fees are really expensive.

349
00:22:28,889 --> 00:22:30,724
Besides, Mi-sook and I were really close.

350
00:22:32,350 --> 00:22:34,352
The father claims
the company played no part,

351
00:22:34,936 --> 00:22:36,438
while his daughter pays the hospital bill.

352
00:22:36,521 --> 00:22:38,023
Are you playing arsonist and firefighter?

353
00:22:38,857 --> 00:22:40,776
It's all Kang Pil-beom's money anyway.

354
00:22:40,859 --> 00:22:42,652
Do you know how he made all that money?

355
00:22:43,320 --> 00:22:44,613
How did he make it…

356
00:22:45,155 --> 00:22:45,989
ma'am?

357
00:22:46,448 --> 00:22:47,491
How do you know, big sis?

358
00:22:47,574 --> 00:22:48,784
Don't call me that.

359
00:22:48,867 --> 00:22:50,243
But you're ten years older than me.

360
00:22:50,327 --> 00:22:51,787
Both of you, stop it.

361
00:22:52,454 --> 00:22:53,497
Let her pay.

362
00:22:53,580 --> 00:22:55,624
That won't even make a dent
in her account.

363
00:23:08,428 --> 00:23:10,472
STRICT BED REST
KIM MI-SOOK

364
00:23:24,444 --> 00:23:25,612
Mi-sook…

365
00:23:25,695 --> 00:23:27,447
Besides, Mi-sook and I were really close.

366
00:23:50,387 --> 00:23:52,889
HANMIN INVESTMENT & SECURITIES

367
00:23:52,973 --> 00:23:54,099
Kang Nora?

368
00:23:54,182 --> 00:23:55,267
Who's that?

369
00:23:55,350 --> 00:23:56,351
Who could she be?

370
00:23:59,729 --> 00:24:01,898
NOTICE OF NEW APPOINTMENT:
EFFECTIVE DECEMBER 15, 1997

371
00:24:01,982 --> 00:24:04,192
NAME: KANG NORA
POSITION: DIRECTOR

372
00:24:29,676 --> 00:24:31,386
Myeong-hwi and I were close friends.

373
00:24:32,721 --> 00:24:33,930
Any sister of his

374
00:24:34,472 --> 00:24:35,891
is a sister of mine too.

375
00:24:37,017 --> 00:24:40,061
I wonder if that princess over there
feels the same way.

376
00:24:41,897 --> 00:24:45,567
You know,
she looks familiar for some reason.

377
00:24:45,650 --> 00:24:46,902
TO THE WORLD, TO THE FUTURE
HANMIN INVESTMENT & SECURITIES

378
00:25:01,041 --> 00:25:02,667
She was the chairman's only daughter?

379
00:25:02,751 --> 00:25:03,585
I'm so jealous.

380
00:25:04,377 --> 00:25:05,670
She'll inherit the company, right?

381
00:25:06,838 --> 00:25:07,714
Is she married?

382
00:25:07,797 --> 00:25:10,300
I don't know about that,
but I read on Yeouido Pirates

383
00:25:10,383 --> 00:25:12,552
that she used to be a successful
Wall Street fund manager.

384
00:25:12,636 --> 00:25:13,470
Really?

385
00:25:14,471 --> 00:25:15,639
What a joke.

386
00:25:19,017 --> 00:25:20,185
Congratulations.

387
00:25:20,268 --> 00:25:21,102
Thank you.

388
00:25:23,939 --> 00:25:24,856
Oh, right.

389
00:25:26,608 --> 00:25:28,276
-It's an honor to serve you.
-I'm honored.

390
00:25:28,360 --> 00:25:29,778
-Congratulations.
-You too.

391
00:25:29,861 --> 00:25:31,738
-Congratulations.
-Yes, congratulations.

392
00:25:31,821 --> 00:25:33,782
-I'll do my very best!
-I'll do my best too.

393
00:25:34,866 --> 00:25:35,700
Hello.

394
00:25:40,789 --> 00:25:44,668
Kang Eun-joo got a score of 210…

395
00:25:45,502 --> 00:25:46,586
I mean, 21 points.

396
00:25:47,212 --> 00:25:48,213
Apple!

397
00:25:48,713 --> 00:25:51,007
It's Apple.

398
00:25:51,091 --> 00:25:53,510
The clueless entry-level minion
from the Trading Division?

399
00:25:53,593 --> 00:25:56,012
And the lowest score on the written exam?

400
00:25:56,096 --> 00:25:57,472
It's you? Ma'am?

401
00:25:57,555 --> 00:25:58,932
Hello, sir.

402
00:26:02,394 --> 00:26:04,521
Who are you calling clueless?

403
00:26:04,604 --> 00:26:06,564
So what if she scored the lowest?

404
00:26:06,648 --> 00:26:07,983
Forget it. You may all leave.

405
00:26:08,566 --> 00:26:09,526
Go on, leave.

406
00:26:09,609 --> 00:26:11,319
The written…

407
00:26:22,122 --> 00:26:23,999
Don't let it upset you, my darling.

408
00:26:24,708 --> 00:26:26,835
What should we have for lunch?

409
00:26:26,918 --> 00:26:27,961
Should we call Mr. Shin?

410
00:26:28,545 --> 00:26:30,672
No, I don't have an appetite.

411
00:26:31,256 --> 00:26:32,090
What?

412
00:26:33,216 --> 00:26:34,050
Gosh.

413
00:26:35,051 --> 00:26:36,219
You don't have an appetite?

414
00:26:37,053 --> 00:26:37,887
That's great.

415
00:26:37,971 --> 00:26:40,849
Let's go all out for this diet.

416
00:26:43,018 --> 00:26:43,852
Nora.

417
00:26:43,935 --> 00:26:47,022
If anyone bothers you at work
or gives you a hard time,

418
00:26:47,105 --> 00:26:48,273
just let me know.

419
00:26:49,149 --> 00:26:52,527
There's nothing I can't do
if it's for you.

420
00:26:57,282 --> 00:27:00,827
Ms. Song Ju-ran and I are joining forces

421
00:27:00,910 --> 00:27:03,163
to make sure you become the chairwoman.

422
00:27:03,872 --> 00:27:05,957
So do as she says, okay?

423
00:27:06,875 --> 00:27:08,001
Okay.

424
00:27:08,710 --> 00:27:09,669
That's my girl.

425
00:27:48,583 --> 00:27:50,210
Queen Bee, have you been well?

426
00:27:52,003 --> 00:27:53,630
I'm back to work starting today.

427
00:27:53,713 --> 00:27:55,256
We ran into each other earlier.

428
00:27:57,092 --> 00:27:58,468
Director Kang Nora.

429
00:27:59,928 --> 00:28:02,555
Have you ratted out
Hong Jang-mi or Go Bok-hee

430
00:28:02,639 --> 00:28:04,140
to your mother?

431
00:28:04,891 --> 00:28:07,185
No, I'm surprisingly loyal.

432
00:28:08,478 --> 00:28:10,397
I do hope you remain loyal.

433
00:28:10,980 --> 00:28:12,232
Especially

434
00:28:12,315 --> 00:28:13,525
when it comes to Hong Jang-mi.

435
00:28:19,406 --> 00:28:20,698
By the way,

436
00:28:21,449 --> 00:28:22,951
is Bom doing all right?

437
00:28:23,701 --> 00:28:24,577
Does she ask for me?

438
00:28:29,958 --> 00:28:30,959
She does not, ma'am.

439
00:28:44,597 --> 00:28:49,310
FEMALE EMPLOYEES' LOCKER ROOM

440
00:28:54,899 --> 00:28:56,192
Where is Bom right now?

441
00:29:12,459 --> 00:29:15,086
Why would the director,
who doesn't even wear a uniform,

442
00:29:15,170 --> 00:29:16,296
come in here?

443
00:29:17,338 --> 00:29:20,550
Just do as your parents say
and behave yourself on the 12th floor.

444
00:29:22,302 --> 00:29:23,636
You're worried about Bom?

445
00:29:23,720 --> 00:29:26,306
You left with your mom
and never looked back!

446
00:29:39,819 --> 00:29:41,946
You're no better
than the trio who bullied you!

447
00:29:42,530 --> 00:29:43,364
You're so mean.

448
00:29:44,073 --> 00:29:46,493
I'll find Bom and bring her to my place!

449
00:29:46,576 --> 00:29:47,577
Hey!

450
00:29:49,245 --> 00:29:50,205
That little…

451
00:30:01,341 --> 00:30:02,175
Ms. Hong.

452
00:30:03,802 --> 00:30:04,719
Are you working late?

453
00:30:06,471 --> 00:30:08,389
Big Al, aren't you going home?

454
00:30:30,328 --> 00:30:31,162
I used to complain

455
00:30:31,746 --> 00:30:33,998
that this office
felt like some tiny rented room,

456
00:30:34,916 --> 00:30:36,417
but now I find it so comforting.

457
00:30:52,642 --> 00:30:54,060
This is the first time I'm speaking today.

458
00:30:54,811 --> 00:30:57,146
The Trading Division
treats me like I'm invisible.

459
00:30:58,273 --> 00:31:00,608
Ms. Hong, I heard
you work for three divisions now.

460
00:31:01,109 --> 00:31:02,277
Isn't it tough?

461
00:31:02,360 --> 00:31:03,736
I'm just doing what I have to.

462
00:31:03,820 --> 00:31:04,946
I'll have to get used to it.

463
00:31:12,078 --> 00:31:13,663
You're still the head of a division.

464
00:31:13,746 --> 00:31:15,373
You should hold weekly meetings

465
00:31:15,456 --> 00:31:17,792
and offer encouraging words
in the morning.

466
00:31:19,085 --> 00:31:20,837
I overheard in the men's room

467
00:31:20,920 --> 00:31:23,298
that when the traders see you come in,

468
00:31:23,381 --> 00:31:26,050
that's how they know it's nine o'clock
and get to work.

469
00:31:26,134 --> 00:31:28,136
You know I'm never late.

470
00:31:28,219 --> 00:31:29,345
Right, Mr. Bang?

471
00:31:39,939 --> 00:31:41,274
I should head out now.

472
00:31:45,987 --> 00:31:46,988
Get home safe.

473
00:31:48,114 --> 00:31:48,948
Goodbye, Ms. Hong.

474
00:31:54,746 --> 00:31:57,540
Ms. Hong is so mature for her age.

475
00:32:00,043 --> 00:32:02,754
She has experience and wisdom
that a 20-year-old can't have.

476
00:32:02,837 --> 00:32:04,005
Yeah.

477
00:32:04,088 --> 00:32:05,506
She's quite big-hearted too.

478
00:32:06,215 --> 00:32:09,135
She seems cold on the outside,
but her heart remains warm.

479
00:32:09,218 --> 00:32:11,012
She really feels like
the senior sometimes.

480
00:32:11,638 --> 00:32:13,431
Yeah, I agree.

481
00:32:16,768 --> 00:32:17,810
Show respect to your senior.

482
00:32:18,728 --> 00:32:19,604
Senior?

483
00:32:23,775 --> 00:32:25,193
That day, Mr. Bang definitely said…

484
00:32:25,276 --> 00:32:27,612
He said she was senior to us.

485
00:32:29,489 --> 00:32:30,823
-No way.
-Come on now.

486
00:32:30,907 --> 00:32:32,533
-Of course not.
-How could she be?

487
00:32:32,617 --> 00:32:33,493
Come on now.

488
00:32:34,243 --> 00:32:35,578
Gosh, Mr. Bang can be so silly.

489
00:32:51,970 --> 00:32:53,680
-Mr. Lee.
-Yes?

490
00:32:55,056 --> 00:32:55,890
Maybe one drink?

491
00:32:56,474 --> 00:32:57,809
Seriously?

492
00:32:58,810 --> 00:33:00,311
Just one.

493
00:33:11,948 --> 00:33:13,282
Big Al.

494
00:33:13,366 --> 00:33:14,826
-Let's go.
-Yeah, let's go.

495
00:33:31,884 --> 00:33:34,679
Director Yun,
you really need to stop calling me.

496
00:33:34,762 --> 00:33:35,972
Listen.

497
00:33:36,055 --> 00:33:38,516
I called for a reason.

498
00:33:39,142 --> 00:33:41,519
I heard Hanmin issued short-term bonds.

499
00:33:42,353 --> 00:33:45,982
A private equity firm in Hong Kong
called DK Ventures bought in bulk,

500
00:33:46,065 --> 00:33:47,775
and other firms bought some as well.

501
00:33:48,484 --> 00:33:51,279
But you know, DK Ventures

502
00:33:51,362 --> 00:33:53,448
is where Shin Jung-woo used to work.

503
00:33:59,454 --> 00:34:01,330
I'll call you back later.

504
00:34:18,389 --> 00:34:20,683
Are you here as a company representative?

505
00:34:20,767 --> 00:34:21,601
No.

506
00:34:23,102 --> 00:34:24,437
Then what are you doing here?

507
00:34:26,314 --> 00:34:27,899
I told you, Ms. Song is looking into you.

508
00:34:28,900 --> 00:34:30,526
I gave you several chances already.

509
00:34:31,110 --> 00:34:32,945
Are you just refusing
to return empty-handed?

510
00:34:35,239 --> 00:34:37,075
How are you so sure that I'm empty-handed?

511
00:34:38,201 --> 00:34:39,368
You don't have it.

512
00:34:40,161 --> 00:34:41,537
Back then and even now,

513
00:34:41,621 --> 00:34:43,331
you don't have what it takes
to face Chairman Kang.

514
00:34:52,632 --> 00:34:54,801
That's for the hospital bills.
Tell me if you need more.

515
00:34:55,510 --> 00:34:57,053
Don't waste your time…

516
00:34:58,596 --> 00:34:59,847
on misplaced sympathy.

517
00:35:16,614 --> 00:35:18,616
I just came for a short hospital visit.

518
00:35:22,120 --> 00:35:23,579
Don't get any wild ideas.

519
00:35:23,663 --> 00:35:26,499
I only turned a blind eye
so she'd submit the untampered financials.

520
00:35:27,625 --> 00:35:29,627
It got Chairman Kang off our back,

521
00:35:29,710 --> 00:35:31,295
so she should at least be compensated.

522
00:35:36,634 --> 00:35:37,802
I don't have what it takes?

523
00:35:39,095 --> 00:35:41,597
Then did you use me
because you had what it took?

524
00:35:42,306 --> 00:35:44,684
By throwing me on the task force
and playing dumb about the files?

525
00:35:46,018 --> 00:35:47,311
You were after the same result.

526
00:35:47,395 --> 00:35:48,729
And what did I want exactly?

527
00:35:50,314 --> 00:35:52,608
The girl in there
is someone I used to live with.

528
00:35:53,317 --> 00:35:56,904
What do you know about the guilt
of thinking that I'm the one to blame?

529
00:35:58,531 --> 00:36:00,032
It wasn't your responsibility.

530
00:36:00,616 --> 00:36:02,535
How have you not changed at all
in nine years?

531
00:36:04,453 --> 00:36:05,872
Why shoulder the burden of something

532
00:36:06,789 --> 00:36:08,082
that's not your responsibility?

533
00:36:10,293 --> 00:36:12,378
Because I don't want
to be pathetic like you.

534
00:36:14,380 --> 00:36:16,174
Back then and even now…

535
00:36:18,217 --> 00:36:19,385
you're just a coward.

536
00:36:51,250 --> 00:36:53,002
Auntie, that hurts.

537
00:36:53,085 --> 00:36:54,086
Does it?

538
00:36:57,632 --> 00:37:00,009
Filling in for your mom is no easy feat.

539
00:37:02,553 --> 00:37:03,638
Sorry.

540
00:37:03,721 --> 00:37:05,473
Of course, it isn't.

541
00:37:05,556 --> 00:37:08,434
My mom, Kim Mi-sook, is special.

542
00:37:10,228 --> 00:37:11,270
You're right.

543
00:37:11,354 --> 00:37:13,648
She is special, so she'll wake up soon.

544
00:37:13,731 --> 00:37:15,441
Just like Snow White?

545
00:37:16,567 --> 00:37:17,568
What?

546
00:37:17,652 --> 00:37:20,696
Like Snow White and like Sleeping Beauty.

547
00:37:22,156 --> 00:37:23,282
Mi-sook will wake up.

548
00:37:23,866 --> 00:37:27,161
The life of a princess
is a lonely and exhausting one.

549
00:37:27,245 --> 00:37:28,704
But you have to endure it.

550
00:37:29,205 --> 00:37:31,707
Bom, go to the small room
and read your fairy tale book.

551
00:37:31,791 --> 00:37:33,000
The aunties need to chat.

552
00:37:33,584 --> 00:37:34,752
Okay.

553
00:37:40,841 --> 00:37:42,134
Hong Keum-bo,

554
00:37:42,218 --> 00:37:44,679
you may be intelligent,
but you lack improvisational skills.

555
00:37:45,930 --> 00:37:47,556
Have you thought about my proposal?

556
00:37:48,516 --> 00:37:49,809
Let's clear a few things first.

557
00:37:51,060 --> 00:37:51,936
One,

558
00:37:52,520 --> 00:37:53,896
which slush fund will we steal first?

559
00:37:55,064 --> 00:37:57,316
The one hidden under the names
of the OW award winners.

560
00:37:59,110 --> 00:37:59,986
Don't tell me

561
00:38:00,069 --> 00:38:01,946
you knew about it from the start.

562
00:38:02,029 --> 00:38:03,739
Was that why you asked for a nomination?

563
00:38:04,490 --> 00:38:05,616
Of course.

564
00:38:08,119 --> 00:38:11,038
Do you remember
that obituary on the intranet system?

565
00:38:11,122 --> 00:38:12,707
Of Kim I-gyeong, the OW award winner?

566
00:38:14,166 --> 00:38:15,084
She died.

567
00:38:16,252 --> 00:38:18,212
That puts both you
and your sister in danger.

568
00:38:19,213 --> 00:38:20,298
Now my second question.

569
00:38:20,381 --> 00:38:22,425
What will you do
with the real Hong Jang-mi

570
00:38:22,508 --> 00:38:23,759
during this operation?

571
00:38:24,719 --> 00:38:25,970
Don't worry.

572
00:38:26,053 --> 00:38:29,098
The real Hong Jang-mi
is in a very safe place.

573
00:38:33,227 --> 00:38:36,230
PERFECT FOR COLLEGE ADMISSION SUCCESS!
SANGOL BOARDING CRAM SCHOOL!

574
00:38:46,198 --> 00:38:47,450
How is this even possible?

575
00:38:53,664 --> 00:38:54,665
HONG JANG-MI

576
00:39:20,983 --> 00:39:23,277
Lie low at the boarding cram school
for three months.

577
00:39:23,986 --> 00:39:26,781
No outings are allowed, day or overnight.

578
00:39:40,628 --> 00:39:42,129
Even so, you can't do this.

579
00:39:43,506 --> 00:39:45,716
Why is everyone telling me
that I can't and shouldn't?

580
00:39:45,800 --> 00:39:46,801
Because it's dangerous.

581
00:39:47,843 --> 00:39:50,262
The fear that President Kang's death
might be on me

582
00:39:50,346 --> 00:39:51,514
keeps me up at night.

583
00:39:52,264 --> 00:39:55,309
Do you know how I ended up at Hanmin
after wandering the country?

584
00:39:55,393 --> 00:39:57,144
Song Ju-ran summoned me.

585
00:39:57,228 --> 00:40:00,231
She hired me on the condition
that I spy on President Kang.

586
00:40:01,023 --> 00:40:01,857
And now,

587
00:40:01,941 --> 00:40:03,609
she wants me to bug President Shin.

588
00:40:12,576 --> 00:40:14,495
I knew Chairman Kang would say that.

589
00:40:14,578 --> 00:40:16,747
He's stingy with his own,

590
00:40:16,831 --> 00:40:19,208
but happy to rack up debt
with other people's money.

591
00:40:20,751 --> 00:40:23,879
He'll issue short-term bonds
with a one-year maturity,

592
00:40:23,963 --> 00:40:26,549
then ask to extend the repayment period
by another year or two.

593
00:40:27,133 --> 00:40:30,177
In the meantime,
we'll quietly accumulate more bonds.

594
00:40:30,761 --> 00:40:32,763
And if Hanmin goes bankrupt on its own?
That's a win for us.

595
00:40:36,892 --> 00:40:37,977
What does that mean?

596
00:40:38,060 --> 00:40:39,270
You understood, right?

597
00:40:40,187 --> 00:40:43,190
When a company goes bankrupt,
the bondholders become its owner.

598
00:40:43,274 --> 00:40:47,069
That's why Shin Jung-woo and DK Ventures
are buying up Hanmin bonds.

599
00:40:47,945 --> 00:40:51,740
They're betting on Hanmin's demise,
based on inside information.

600
00:40:52,741 --> 00:40:54,577
They intend to snap up
the company for cheap.

601
00:40:55,995 --> 00:40:57,621
You can't trust any of them.

602
00:40:58,581 --> 00:41:01,250
Forget the ledger,
this is completely out of our league.

603
00:41:01,959 --> 00:41:05,254
I'm going to the hospital tonight
to say goodbye to Mi-sook.

604
00:41:05,838 --> 00:41:07,548
I'm officially rejecting your proposal.

605
00:41:16,682 --> 00:41:17,516
Gosh.

606
00:41:17,600 --> 00:41:19,393
You're home, as expected.

607
00:41:20,060 --> 00:41:22,104
Eun-joo, who used to live here,
called me today.

608
00:41:23,606 --> 00:41:24,773
Eun-joo did?

609
00:41:25,691 --> 00:41:27,651
Is that Auntie Eun-joo?

610
00:41:27,735 --> 00:41:28,611
No.

611
00:41:52,343 --> 00:41:53,594
I do think

612
00:41:54,512 --> 00:41:56,514
what happened to Mi-sook is a tragedy,

613
00:41:56,597 --> 00:41:58,849
but we are a dormitory
supported by the city

614
00:41:59,350 --> 00:42:01,852
that helps unmarried women
achieve independence.

615
00:42:02,770 --> 00:42:04,813
As such, all rules must be followed.

616
00:42:05,731 --> 00:42:08,943
Outsiders are strictly forbidden
in this dormitory.

617
00:42:10,402 --> 00:42:12,196
Even if it's…

618
00:42:14,281 --> 00:42:15,324
a resident's child.

619
00:42:18,577 --> 00:42:19,411
Sorry.

620
00:42:20,704 --> 00:42:23,123
You two must figure out
what will be best for her.

621
00:42:23,207 --> 00:42:25,084
After all, neither of you is her guardian.

622
00:42:31,882 --> 00:42:34,260
I'll go back to the children's home.

623
00:42:35,135 --> 00:42:37,805
So please don't get mad at the aunties.

624
00:42:51,235 --> 00:42:52,987
I have a child here…

625
00:42:53,070 --> 00:42:56,323
We're unable to take in
any more children right now.

626
00:42:56,824 --> 00:42:58,701
I see.

627
00:42:58,784 --> 00:43:01,537
All facilities have been full
since the IMF crisis began.

628
00:43:01,620 --> 00:43:02,871
I see.

629
00:43:03,455 --> 00:43:04,540
I'm sorry.

630
00:43:12,798 --> 00:43:15,217
I was wondering
if you could take in a child.

631
00:43:17,386 --> 00:43:19,555
Thank you. I'll call you back in a bit.

632
00:43:21,849 --> 00:43:23,559
I found a spot.

633
00:43:24,143 --> 00:43:25,436
We can drop Bom off tomorrow.

634
00:43:26,353 --> 00:43:27,896
The RA is right.

635
00:43:27,980 --> 00:43:29,481
We can't be responsible for her.

636
00:43:30,983 --> 00:43:32,651
Don't say that when she can hear you.

637
00:43:32,735 --> 00:43:35,946
How would you pull off a massive task
when you can't even take care of a child?

638
00:43:42,411 --> 00:43:43,454
I knew from the start

639
00:43:44,538 --> 00:43:46,665
that the New Korea Fund had issues.

640
00:43:47,833 --> 00:43:50,044
But I couldn't stop Mi-sook.

641
00:43:50,878 --> 00:43:51,920
No, I didn't stop her.

642
00:43:52,713 --> 00:43:54,465
Because my work was more important.

643
00:43:57,217 --> 00:43:58,886
The fact that I was one of those people

644
00:43:59,887 --> 00:44:02,181
who refused to take responsibility
makes me so mad.

645
00:44:04,642 --> 00:44:05,601
I can't do it.

646
00:44:18,072 --> 00:44:19,615
I'll be your guardian from now on,

647
00:44:20,199 --> 00:44:21,784
just until your mom gets better.

648
00:44:22,826 --> 00:44:25,204
We can't live here together,

649
00:44:25,704 --> 00:44:27,456
but I think we can try something else.

650
00:44:52,564 --> 00:44:53,732
Eat up.

651
00:44:55,234 --> 00:44:56,819
Now that everyone is here,

652
00:44:57,861 --> 00:44:58,695
cheers!

653
00:44:58,779 --> 00:45:00,155
-Cheers.
-Cheers.

654
00:45:01,698 --> 00:45:03,659
-Have a good dinner.
-Thank you.

655
00:45:07,621 --> 00:45:08,914
Did our President Shin

656
00:45:09,665 --> 00:45:11,375
date a lot of women in Hong Kong?

657
00:45:12,876 --> 00:45:14,670
All he ever did was work,
so I worried about him.

658
00:45:16,422 --> 00:45:19,883
He would never reveal
his ally's weaknesses.

659
00:45:19,967 --> 00:45:20,801
It's the truth.

660
00:45:22,177 --> 00:45:23,637
His last relationship was nine years ago.

661
00:45:23,720 --> 00:45:25,806
I think he said
they were college sweethearts.

662
00:45:26,473 --> 00:45:27,307
Really?

663
00:45:28,976 --> 00:45:29,852
How classic.

664
00:45:31,270 --> 00:45:34,440
Yes, he's one tidy person.

665
00:45:45,117 --> 00:45:47,119
Wait, was that your sandglass?

666
00:45:48,620 --> 00:45:49,830
Well,

667
00:45:49,913 --> 00:45:51,331
that was a long time ago.

668
00:45:52,291 --> 00:45:53,459
If it was nine years ago,

669
00:45:53,542 --> 00:45:55,127
she must have a kid or two by now.

670
00:45:55,627 --> 00:45:56,587
Yeah, probably.

671
00:45:58,464 --> 00:45:59,298
Now,

672
00:46:00,215 --> 00:46:02,468
I also have exciting news
about President Shin and Nora.

673
00:46:03,677 --> 00:46:04,887
On January 16th,

674
00:46:05,471 --> 00:46:06,597
the two are getting engaged.

675
00:46:09,016 --> 00:46:10,601
Surprise, you two.

676
00:46:10,684 --> 00:46:12,519
The chairman gave his blessing.

677
00:46:13,228 --> 00:46:14,855
Congratulations.

678
00:46:14,938 --> 00:46:16,482
Cheers. You'll be there, right?

679
00:46:16,565 --> 00:46:18,358
Congratulations, you two.

680
00:46:20,777 --> 00:46:21,904
Congrats, Auntie.

681
00:46:23,489 --> 00:46:25,782
I guess you'll really be our family soon.

682
00:46:30,621 --> 00:46:31,788
Congratulations, Ms. Kang.

683
00:46:38,587 --> 00:46:41,089
CLOSED DUE TO A FAMILY EMERGENCY

684
00:46:59,566 --> 00:47:00,484
You know,

685
00:47:01,652 --> 00:47:05,572
our Keum-bo is pretty overall,
but her eyes especially sparkle like gems

686
00:47:05,656 --> 00:47:07,950
because she gets them from me.

687
00:47:08,033 --> 00:47:09,785
If you look closely,

688
00:47:10,285 --> 00:47:12,496
this kid has got gems in her eyes too.

689
00:47:12,579 --> 00:47:16,250
Twinkle, twinkle, little star

690
00:47:18,085 --> 00:47:20,963
-Could it be…
-Your imagination is running wild.

691
00:47:21,046 --> 00:47:21,922
You're wrong.

692
00:47:23,423 --> 00:47:24,716
Sweetie,

693
00:47:24,800 --> 00:47:28,845
can you tell me the name of the woman
who gave birth to you and raised you?

694
00:47:29,429 --> 00:47:31,765
It's Ms. Kim Mi-sook.

695
00:47:32,349 --> 00:47:33,350
Mi-sook…

696
00:47:34,268 --> 00:47:36,478
She's my colleague's daughter.

697
00:47:36,562 --> 00:47:38,730
I brought her here
because she has nowhere to go.

698
00:47:39,273 --> 00:47:41,316
Her mom's in the hospital,

699
00:47:42,234 --> 00:47:43,193
and she's still unconscious.

700
00:47:43,777 --> 00:47:46,238
-My goodness.
-The children's homes are full too.

701
00:47:46,321 --> 00:47:47,781
There are no empty spots.

702
00:47:47,864 --> 00:47:48,865
Oh dear.

703
00:47:49,866 --> 00:47:52,703
I guess the IMF crisis
has more parents dropping off their kids.

704
00:47:53,579 --> 00:47:56,456
I know you're busy with the restaurant,
so I'm sorry to ask you this.

705
00:47:56,540 --> 00:47:59,626
Don't be sorry. We're not busy.

706
00:47:59,710 --> 00:48:01,336
Don't worry about the kid either.

707
00:48:01,420 --> 00:48:03,589
Of course you should leave her with us.

708
00:48:03,672 --> 00:48:05,799
We raised two wild,
unruly sisters ourselves.

709
00:48:07,217 --> 00:48:08,552
By the way,

710
00:48:08,635 --> 00:48:11,138
how'd it go with that young man last time?

711
00:48:12,431 --> 00:48:13,849
You know,

712
00:48:13,932 --> 00:48:16,393
the handsome man
you told us to zip our lips about.

713
00:48:16,977 --> 00:48:18,061
He died.

714
00:48:21,898 --> 00:48:22,899
Bom, have some more.

715
00:48:23,483 --> 00:48:25,152
Yeah, eat up.

716
00:48:26,153 --> 00:48:27,070
Have this too.

717
00:48:27,154 --> 00:48:28,905
Thank you.

718
00:48:31,575 --> 00:48:32,618
Thanks.

719
00:48:32,701 --> 00:48:34,036
Goodness me.

720
00:48:34,703 --> 00:48:35,954
All thanks to Mi-sook's child,

721
00:48:36,038 --> 00:48:38,957
we get to hear our daughter
apologize and thank us.

722
00:48:41,710 --> 00:48:42,586
What's your name?

723
00:48:42,669 --> 00:48:43,837
It's Bom.

724
00:48:43,920 --> 00:48:46,173
-Gosh. Bom.
-Hello, Bom.

725
00:48:48,258 --> 00:48:49,926
-Is it good?
-Yes.

726
00:48:50,636 --> 00:48:51,470
Eat up.

727
00:48:57,351 --> 00:49:01,605
ULLALA CHICKEN

728
00:49:08,612 --> 00:49:11,156
Why did you follow us
if you weren't going to come in?

729
00:49:12,074 --> 00:49:13,700
I needed time to think.

730
00:49:14,826 --> 00:49:15,661
It's cold.

731
00:49:17,079 --> 00:49:18,121
I told you to come inside.

732
00:49:18,205 --> 00:49:22,042
How can I, when your parents think
I'm Hong Jang-mi's senior alum?

733
00:49:23,669 --> 00:49:24,920
Let's part ways here.

734
00:49:25,671 --> 00:49:26,505
Have a nice life.

735
00:49:28,173 --> 00:49:30,175
Thank you for everything, Go Bok-hee.

736
00:49:32,219 --> 00:49:35,389
After being called Ms. Go
and Queen Bee all this time,

737
00:49:35,972 --> 00:49:37,224
I'm Go Bok-hee in the end.

738
00:50:09,965 --> 00:50:10,799
Damn it.

739
00:50:11,341 --> 00:50:12,217
Come on.

740
00:50:25,731 --> 00:50:28,442
I'm not a kid.
What am I supposed to do with this?

741
00:50:35,323 --> 00:50:36,533
Hong Jang-mi.

742
00:50:36,616 --> 00:50:40,203
As of today, you're officially recognized
as a resident of Room 301.

743
00:50:40,287 --> 00:50:41,997
"We're college students."

744
00:50:47,294 --> 00:50:48,545
Bok-hee, wait.

745
00:50:49,379 --> 00:50:51,965
This is pepper spray for self-defense,

746
00:50:52,048 --> 00:50:53,633
and this is your lunch.

747
00:50:55,135 --> 00:50:57,387
Bok-hee, I'm always praying for you.

748
00:50:58,263 --> 00:51:00,724
My mommy prays every day.

749
00:51:34,424 --> 00:51:35,258
Why didn't you stop me?

750
00:51:36,843 --> 00:51:39,638
You'd never be able to
steal that money by yourself.

751
00:51:41,097 --> 00:51:41,932
Are you interested?

752
00:51:48,647 --> 00:51:49,689
Walk me through the plan.

753
00:51:50,690 --> 00:51:52,692
Steal 300 billion won and then what?

754
00:51:53,985 --> 00:51:56,905
Shin Jung-woo is betting
on Hanmin going belly up.

755
00:51:56,988 --> 00:51:58,156
Are you doing the same?

756
00:52:01,952 --> 00:52:03,787
I'm going to save Hanmin.

757
00:52:09,751 --> 00:52:12,546
If you look at
Hanmin's ownership structure,

758
00:52:12,629 --> 00:52:14,422
Oh Deok-gyu has 9%

759
00:52:14,506 --> 00:52:16,383
and Choi In-ja has 1%.

760
00:52:16,466 --> 00:52:19,928
Oh Deok-gyu inherited his shares
after his wife passed away,

761
00:52:20,011 --> 00:52:23,265
while Choi In-ja got hers from Kang
as a part of her divorce settlement.

762
00:52:25,433 --> 00:52:27,435
Kang Nora, his only daughter, has 5%

763
00:52:27,519 --> 00:52:29,396
and so does his grandson Albert.

764
00:52:30,146 --> 00:52:34,317
After Kang Myeong-hwi died,
his 9% went to his father,

765
00:52:34,401 --> 00:52:36,945
which leaves Kang Pil-beom with 48.6%.

766
00:52:37,696 --> 00:52:40,532
So if all the shares
in his family are combined,

767
00:52:40,615 --> 00:52:42,033
they have 68.6%.

768
00:52:42,534 --> 00:52:45,412
Hanmin is basically
a family-owned business.

769
00:52:45,495 --> 00:52:46,913
In other words,

770
00:52:46,997 --> 00:52:49,457
Hanmin is Kang Pil-beom's kingdom.

771
00:52:50,667 --> 00:52:52,502
You've been a goody-two-shoes
your whole life,

772
00:52:52,586 --> 00:52:55,213
so how would you steal
that massive amount of money?

773
00:52:55,714 --> 00:52:56,548
Teach me.

774
00:52:56,631 --> 00:52:58,341
I'm a fast learner.

775
00:52:59,467 --> 00:53:00,969
Unlike Shin Jung-woo,

776
00:53:01,052 --> 00:53:03,722
we'll steal the slush fund
and buy Hanmin's stocks.

777
00:53:05,682 --> 00:53:07,809
That'll take away
Kang Pil-beom's management rights,

778
00:53:07,893 --> 00:53:10,687
and blow up Shin Jung-woo
and DK Ventures's theft.

779
00:53:12,314 --> 00:53:16,192
Then we'll be able to protect
both Hanmin and its employees.

780
00:53:20,447 --> 00:53:24,200
I'm not interested in destroying them
or in saving the company.

781
00:53:25,076 --> 00:53:27,746
Set some aside for Mi-sook's
hospital bills and compensation,

782
00:53:27,829 --> 00:53:29,581
and give me a little hazard pay.

783
00:53:30,624 --> 00:53:31,750
If you can promise me that,

784
00:53:31,833 --> 00:53:33,752
I'm in with Hong Keum-bo.

785
00:53:35,462 --> 00:53:37,047
How much is a little hazard pay…

786
00:53:38,298 --> 00:53:39,382
exactly?

787
00:53:40,342 --> 00:53:41,551
Maybe 10%?

788
00:53:41,635 --> 00:53:42,469
Ten?

789
00:53:43,637 --> 00:53:45,388
Have you no shame?

790
00:53:46,514 --> 00:53:47,390
Hold on.

791
00:53:47,933 --> 00:53:49,434
She'll be stealing the slush fund

792
00:53:50,018 --> 00:53:52,187
and also monitoring Shin Jung-woo…

793
00:53:53,021 --> 00:53:53,855
That's right.

794
00:53:54,564 --> 00:53:56,650
You'll be needing Go Bok-hee
for several reasons.

795
00:53:58,693 --> 00:54:00,236
Based on how you do,

796
00:54:00,320 --> 00:54:03,073
I can give you a discount
and only ask for a one-way ticket to LA.

797
00:54:04,324 --> 00:54:07,786
I'll show you
what "the utmost best" looks like.

798
00:54:07,869 --> 00:54:09,537
You just wait and see.

799
00:54:14,751 --> 00:54:16,127
Let's see what the veteran can do.

800
00:54:28,473 --> 00:54:30,016
You have to request time off first.

801
00:54:30,100 --> 00:54:32,978
Cha is hell-bent on revenge
after that fiasco, right?

802
00:54:33,478 --> 00:54:34,688
I'll have to coax him.

803
00:54:35,480 --> 00:54:37,440
Maybe we should've asked
for help from Nora?

804
00:54:37,524 --> 00:54:38,692
He'd listen to a director.

805
00:54:39,651 --> 00:54:41,236
Why are you so submissive to authority?

806
00:54:43,279 --> 00:54:44,406
Everyone's like that.

807
00:54:44,489 --> 00:54:45,448
Everything about you,

808
00:54:45,532 --> 00:54:47,701
from the unyielding integrity
to the petty pride,

809
00:54:47,784 --> 00:54:49,285
needs to go now.

810
00:54:49,369 --> 00:54:52,247
It's hard to earn money,
but it's even harder to steal it.

811
00:54:52,330 --> 00:54:54,541
Especially in this tough economy.

812
00:55:07,262 --> 00:55:09,264
Amid challenges in corporate management,

813
00:55:09,347 --> 00:55:12,100
the burdens on ordinary citizens
are steadily increasing.

814
00:55:12,183 --> 00:55:14,477
Soaring inflation
that shows no sign of slowing

815
00:55:14,561 --> 00:55:16,271
and the threat of widespread unemployment

816
00:55:16,354 --> 00:55:19,357
are raising fears
of an unprecedentedly cold winter ahead.

817
00:55:22,485 --> 00:55:24,195
This place has really thinned out.

818
00:55:24,738 --> 00:55:27,741
Well, a 40% reduction
is basically half the workforce.

819
00:55:29,993 --> 00:55:32,537
By the way,
can we really trust DK Ventures?

820
00:55:33,371 --> 00:55:35,206
-Why do you ask?
-They're treating this place

821
00:55:35,290 --> 00:55:36,249
like occupied territory.

822
00:55:36,833 --> 00:55:39,127
They summon the division managers
and grill them.

823
00:55:39,711 --> 00:55:41,713
There's talk of a second restructuring,

824
00:55:41,796 --> 00:55:43,506
and the air in the office is tense.

825
00:55:44,466 --> 00:55:45,383
Big Al.

826
00:55:45,967 --> 00:55:46,843
Have you heard anything?

827
00:55:47,719 --> 00:55:48,928
Nothing.

828
00:55:49,721 --> 00:55:51,598
I'm sure President Shin
knows what he's doing.

829
00:55:55,226 --> 00:55:57,103
I hear President Shin was the facilitator

830
00:55:57,187 --> 00:56:01,149
who acted as a bridge
between DK Ventures and Hanmin.

831
00:56:02,358 --> 00:56:04,736
That's why his reputation
has been tanking.

832
00:56:04,819 --> 00:56:05,945
Tell us.

833
00:56:17,582 --> 00:56:19,959
I might not look it,
but I respect kinship.

834
00:56:20,460 --> 00:56:23,046
I don't feel comfortable
badmouthing my uncle-to-be.

835
00:56:23,129 --> 00:56:24,005
-Uncle?
-Uncle?

836
00:56:31,888 --> 00:56:32,722
Hey.

837
00:56:32,806 --> 00:56:35,391
-Ms. Hong, this too.
-Sure.

838
00:56:35,475 --> 00:56:37,936
-Ms. Hong, I need four copies of this.
-Sure.

839
00:56:38,019 --> 00:56:39,354
It's all missing.

840
00:56:41,356 --> 00:56:42,190
Seriously?

841
00:56:50,824 --> 00:56:53,326
What's this? I never asked for coffee.

842
00:56:54,077 --> 00:56:55,870
I'd like to take tomorrow off.

843
00:56:56,496 --> 00:56:58,081
I'd also like tomorrow off.

844
00:57:01,918 --> 00:57:04,546
But you see, we can't just do
what we want to do

845
00:57:04,629 --> 00:57:05,755
all the time.

846
00:57:05,839 --> 00:57:07,966
Say goodbye to your day off.

847
00:57:10,635 --> 00:57:11,886
Hold on, Ms. Hong.

848
00:57:11,970 --> 00:57:13,012
Let me ask you something.

849
00:57:14,472 --> 00:57:17,559
Were you close to Director Kang Nora?

850
00:57:17,642 --> 00:57:20,770
I've acquired intel
that you two used to eat burgers together.

851
00:57:22,814 --> 00:57:25,442
Why don't you compile an extensive list

852
00:57:25,525 --> 00:57:27,402
of what Director Kang likes?

853
00:57:33,324 --> 00:57:34,159
Goodbye now.

854
00:57:38,788 --> 00:57:41,708
DIRECTOR KANG NORA'S FAVORITE FOOD
AND PREFERENCES

855
00:57:42,500 --> 00:57:45,128
Will that be enough
for Cha to grant you time off?

856
00:57:47,005 --> 00:57:50,091
You could also go
and make that withdrawal yourself.

857
00:57:52,010 --> 00:57:54,971
Why do I feel like
you're pushing me into danger?

858
00:57:55,680 --> 00:57:57,474
The money in Hong Jang-mi's account

859
00:57:57,557 --> 00:58:00,101
should be withdrawn by the account holder
to avoid suspicion.

860
00:58:00,685 --> 00:58:03,062
Context also matters
in fraud and embezzlement.

861
00:58:04,397 --> 00:58:08,234
Also, I'll be on standby on the 12th floor
in case of an emergency.

862
00:58:08,318 --> 00:58:09,486
There's one person

863
00:58:10,069 --> 00:58:11,279
who could help us with this…

864
00:58:12,780 --> 00:58:14,741
Damn it. I don't want to.

865
00:58:14,824 --> 00:58:16,743
I told you to lose that petty pride.

866
00:58:17,327 --> 00:58:18,286
If you can't do it,

867
00:58:18,369 --> 00:58:20,955
let's make a deal and not a request.

868
00:58:21,581 --> 00:58:24,292
Ms. Song might get
a confirmation call from the bank,

869
00:58:24,375 --> 00:58:27,045
so I'll have Madam Choi
keep her busy with her nagging.

870
00:58:28,505 --> 00:58:29,797
But to make that happen…

871
00:58:29,881 --> 00:58:30,757
KANG NORA

872
00:58:30,840 --> 00:58:32,050
…we need her.

873
00:58:39,265 --> 00:58:40,391
What's taking her so long?

874
00:58:42,018 --> 00:58:43,603
I hear footsteps.

875
00:59:00,828 --> 00:59:03,122
Why did you take the stairs
and not the elevator?

876
00:59:04,249 --> 00:59:07,418
I figured I'd need
to avoid attracting attention

877
00:59:07,502 --> 00:59:09,462
and maintain secrecy.

878
00:59:10,296 --> 00:59:11,589
She's not completely clueless.

879
00:59:21,516 --> 00:59:24,060
I'm just trying to meet your eye level,

880
00:59:24,143 --> 00:59:25,228
big sisters.

881
00:59:28,481 --> 00:59:29,566
You want to see Bom, right?

882
00:59:30,525 --> 00:59:31,609
Yes.

883
00:59:32,151 --> 00:59:33,278
If you fill me in for a day,

884
00:59:33,361 --> 00:59:34,779
I'll tell you where Bom is.

885
00:59:35,363 --> 00:59:36,364
I can totally do that.

886
00:59:37,448 --> 00:59:38,449
But…

887
00:59:38,533 --> 00:59:39,784
what am I filling?

888
00:59:46,624 --> 00:59:49,669
OPERATION DAY

889
01:00:02,473 --> 01:00:03,474
Ms. Hong?

890
01:00:04,058 --> 01:00:04,892
Do you have a cold?

891
01:00:21,284 --> 01:00:22,368
Ms. Hong.

892
01:00:31,336 --> 01:00:32,378
HONG JANG-MI

893
01:00:45,016 --> 01:00:46,059
Auntie?

894
01:00:54,901 --> 01:00:55,985
What are you…

895
01:01:01,240 --> 01:01:02,659
That was so rude of you.

896
01:01:02,742 --> 01:01:05,119
How could you strip me like that?

897
01:01:05,620 --> 01:01:06,496
Strip you?

898
01:01:07,205 --> 01:01:08,665
-No…
-Auntie.

899
01:01:08,748 --> 01:01:10,708
That could lead to a misunderstanding.

900
01:01:10,792 --> 01:01:13,503
Your mask was taken off, not stripped.

901
01:01:14,379 --> 01:01:15,296
It was about her mask.

902
01:01:15,380 --> 01:01:16,756
I see.

903
01:01:20,760 --> 01:01:22,637
I will apologize for that.

904
01:01:23,221 --> 01:01:24,097
I'm sorry.

905
01:01:24,597 --> 01:01:26,683
But you'll also need to explain yourself.

906
01:01:27,684 --> 01:01:30,603
Why were you delivering lunches
with someone else's name tag?

907
01:01:33,314 --> 01:01:36,067
Are you exercising
your right to remain silent?

908
01:01:37,485 --> 01:01:38,736
Ms. Go.

909
01:01:38,820 --> 01:01:40,154
Where's Ms. Hong Jang-mi?

910
01:01:41,864 --> 01:01:45,201
I believe I've mentioned
this several times before,

911
01:01:46,285 --> 01:01:47,161
but we're not friends.

912
01:01:49,831 --> 01:01:51,749
Where else would Ms. Hong be?

913
01:01:51,833 --> 01:01:53,751
I'm sure she's at the hospital
where her roommate is.

914
01:01:53,835 --> 01:01:56,754
She probably couldn't take time off,
so Auntie Nora covered for her.

915
01:01:56,838 --> 01:01:58,548
-Right?
-Right.

916
01:01:59,132 --> 01:01:59,966
He's right.

917
01:02:03,136 --> 01:02:05,513
I have to show up at the IT Division
by three o'clock.

918
01:02:06,013 --> 01:02:07,557
Take care now.

919
01:02:22,780 --> 01:02:23,781
I should get going too.

920
01:02:30,288 --> 01:02:31,414
Is it just me…

921
01:02:33,249 --> 01:02:35,835
or do you seem
particularly interested in Hong Jang-mi?

922
01:02:38,129 --> 01:02:39,464
I can assure you this.

923
01:02:41,007 --> 01:02:44,010
I am most certainly
not interested in Hong Jang-mi.

924
01:02:51,601 --> 01:02:53,102
You got caught by him, of all people?

925
01:02:53,186 --> 01:02:54,604
And your mom? Did you ask her to come?

926
01:02:54,687 --> 01:02:56,355
She should be here soon.

927
01:02:58,900 --> 01:02:59,901
Don't worry about me.

928
01:03:12,079 --> 01:03:13,956
By the way, where did Ms. Hong go?

929
01:03:19,003 --> 01:03:22,215
You have to withdraw funds
from a total of three different banks.

930
01:03:22,298 --> 01:03:25,885
Breaking the large check into smaller ones
makes it harder to trace.

931
01:03:25,968 --> 01:03:27,553
Typically, at lunchtime,

932
01:03:27,637 --> 01:03:30,765
there are fewer tellers working
but more customers.

933
01:03:30,848 --> 01:03:32,642
So they process
deposits and withdrawals quickly

934
01:03:32,725 --> 01:03:34,101
to avoid holding up the line.

935
01:03:34,185 --> 01:03:36,729
That's the time you want to target.

936
01:03:38,898 --> 01:03:40,191
CHUNGSEO BANK

937
01:03:42,193 --> 01:03:45,071
Everyone is saying
you're about to close down for good!

938
01:03:45,154 --> 01:03:48,699
Help me withdraw the funds
from my five-year savings account first!

939
01:03:48,783 --> 01:03:50,409
Hurry up!

940
01:03:57,750 --> 01:04:02,046
My life and my friends' lives
are at stake here!

941
01:04:13,766 --> 01:04:15,810
3 BILLION WON TRANSFERRED

942
01:04:15,893 --> 01:04:18,354
TRANSFER OF 3 BILLION WON!

943
01:04:18,437 --> 01:04:21,566
FARMERS' BANK

944
01:04:24,777 --> 01:04:26,320
FARMERS' BANK
CHECKING ACCOUNT

945
01:04:26,404 --> 01:04:27,947
There's one left now.

946
01:04:28,948 --> 01:04:30,491
The one with the largest balance.

947
01:04:43,087 --> 01:04:44,839
I have to do it today.

948
01:04:47,675 --> 01:04:49,385
I mean, do you think this makes any sense?

949
01:04:49,969 --> 01:04:52,638
My Nora is the only one
without an assistant of her own.

950
01:04:52,722 --> 01:04:54,891
She's not some lightweight executive.

951
01:04:55,641 --> 01:04:58,227
Just imagine how excluded she must feel!

952
01:05:00,521 --> 01:05:01,689
This is ridiculous!

953
01:05:02,565 --> 01:05:05,109
Ms. Song might get
a confirmation call from the bank.

954
01:05:05,192 --> 01:05:08,487
I'll be on standby on the 12th floor
in case of an emergency.

955
01:05:09,697 --> 01:05:12,158
Now serving customer number 217.

956
01:05:12,241 --> 01:05:13,159
That's me!

957
01:05:22,543 --> 01:05:23,794
S.J.R. CONFIRMATION REQUIRED

958
01:05:26,797 --> 01:05:27,924
What's wrong?

959
01:05:28,424 --> 01:05:30,843
It says I need to confirm with an "SJR."

960
01:05:31,677 --> 01:05:32,678
Oh, that.

961
01:05:34,263 --> 01:05:37,725
They sometimes use dual authorization
to hide the dirty money even deeper,

962
01:05:37,808 --> 01:05:40,478
so take Song Ju-ran's
authorization letter, just in case.

963
01:05:41,812 --> 01:05:43,105
"SJR."

964
01:05:43,189 --> 01:05:44,815
It stands for Song Ju-ran, my boss.

965
01:05:46,317 --> 01:05:49,236
That's why she gave me this.

966
01:05:49,320 --> 01:05:50,613
It's an authorization letter.

967
01:05:57,620 --> 01:05:58,996
AUTHORIZATION LETTER

968
01:05:59,580 --> 01:06:01,290
RESIDENT REGISTRATION CARD
HONG JANG-MI

969
01:06:06,295 --> 01:06:07,964
I am indeed Hong Jang-mi.

970
01:06:08,589 --> 01:06:10,925
Yes, we've confirmed your name and face,

971
01:06:11,008 --> 01:06:14,303
but we should be extra careful
with such a large sum of money.

972
01:06:15,846 --> 01:06:16,722
Just a moment.

973
01:06:33,864 --> 01:06:34,824
Madam Choi.

974
01:06:38,077 --> 01:06:39,620
Let's talk in my office.

975
01:07:14,071 --> 01:07:18,034
SPECIAL THANKS TO SHIN YU-NA
FOR HER APPEARANCE

976
01:07:49,106 --> 01:07:50,941
UNDERCOVER MISS HONG

977
01:07:51,525 --> 01:07:53,903
I think that "Captain" knows something.

978
01:07:53,986 --> 01:07:54,862
Who could it be?

979
01:07:54,945 --> 01:07:56,530
We must find them
and get them on our side.

980
01:07:56,614 --> 01:07:57,907
You suspect someone, don't you?

981
01:07:58,491 --> 01:08:00,534
-If it wasn't an insider…
-Yes?

982
01:08:00,618 --> 01:08:02,119
An outsider must have done it?

983
01:08:02,203 --> 01:08:05,372
He needs to get beaten up out there
for him to accept our hand.

984
01:08:05,456 --> 01:08:06,791
And you know what happens next.

985
01:08:06,874 --> 01:08:08,125
Why can't I log in?

986
01:08:08,751 --> 01:08:10,878
Maybe you got banned
for writing something inappropriate?

987
01:08:12,004 --> 01:08:13,422
Hong Keum-bo.

988
01:08:13,506 --> 01:08:14,840
Any updates on Ms. Song?

989
01:08:14,924 --> 01:08:17,218
She'll be on your tail
once she realizes the funds are gone.

990
01:08:17,301 --> 01:08:19,428
Inspector of the Capital Market
Investigation Division at the FSS,

991
01:08:19,512 --> 01:08:20,554
Inspector Hong Keum-bo.

992
01:08:23,307 --> 01:08:28,312
Subtitle translation by: Justin S. Kim

